@node SYSREQ "System Requirements"

Requirements

bsdsocket.library compatible TCP/IP stack

Reasonably complete Amiga DOS 3.0+ installation
 (2.04 may work, but has not been tested.)

Default screen of at least 4 colors
@endnode

@node INSTALL "Installation"
The distribution archive containts a directory structure which
should be maintained. One drawer will be created which contains
the executble, support files, and subdirectory structure. All
files relating to tn3270 are referenced relative to that structure.
To install, simply drag the tn3270 drawer to the desired place
on your system.
@endnode

@node USAGE "Using tn3270"

Usage

From cli: tn3270 hostname

From Workbench: Double click the tn3270 or a @{"prefs" link PREFS} file icon

If hostname is not supplied, by command line or in the prefs,
you will be greeted with the connect window. Enter the desired
host name and port (optional) and click the connect button.

If all goes well, the opening screen from the host will
display. The main portion of the screen is the 3270 area.
The other two components are the normal Amiga @{"menus" link MENUS}  and
the @{"Operator Information Area" link OIA}.

Presently, NVT mode, non-3270 interaction with the host server,
happens in a separate window, which only opens if needed.
@endnode

@node LIMITS "Limitations and Known Bugs"
This is alpha level software. Bugs may abound. I use it often,
and it doesn't crash or do really kinky things to my system.
Experience, however, shows this doesn't prove much. Also, be
aware that this began as a port of a un*x program, and it has
suprised me with how it REALLY works on occasion. With that
in mind, here are some specific limitations.

NVT mode is not yet incorporated into the main screen, and
will occur in a separate window. That window opens on connection
and usually, can be safely closed or flippedto the back.

24x80 only, no color or extended highlight (IBM-3278-2)

Limited read partition query support, and no other WSF commands.

SFE and SA orders are not supported.

The prefs editor and connection directory mentioned in this
document are not yet included in this distribution.

All of these issues will be addressed in time.
@endnode

